title.en-US: Local Food Spots From Our Staff

summary.en-US: We polled our staff for a few local recommendations.

description.en-US:
The first thing you need to know is that CLC lunches and dinners are worth staying for. In case you find yourself in need of another meal, here are a few recommendations from our staff.

### Local Spots
-  Mattito’s
-  Asian Mint
-  Chipotle
-  Torchy’s Tacos (get the queso!)
-  Ten50 BBQ
-  Street's Fine Chicken
-  Shake Shack 
-  Twisted Root

### Quick-Bite Favorites
- Chick-fil-A
- In-N-Out
- Raising Cane’s
- Whataburger
- Pot Belly Sandwich Shop
- Sonic
- Freebirds 

### Dessert
- Cinnaholic
- Steel City Pops
- Frost Gelato

### Breakfast Spots
- Crossroads Diner 
- Maple Leaf Diner 
- Cindi’s New York Deli 

### Looking to Explore Dallas
Trinity Groves, located in a redeveloped portion of West Dallas, not only serves as a multi-eatery “restaurant incubator” with great patio dining, but it also offers a walking bridge and great views of downtown Dallas. (Be sure to stop at Kate Weiser Chocolate, even if it’s only to view her chocolate creations.)

Deep Ellum (east of Downtown) or Bishop Arts (southwest Dallas) are highly walkable, revitalized areas full of culture, shops, and food. I’d personally give the edge to Bishop Arts, but Deep Ellum is edgier, if that’s your scene. If you want to explore a little bit closer in, spend some time on Lower Greenville or wander Mockingbird Station.

summary.en-US: A Special Welcome from Todd Wagner, Senior Pastor & Elder.

description.en-US:
We know that today, God is going to do something in the world to make
His name known. God will change hearts, humble the proud, heal the hurting, and meet critical needs in and through His people. Because we know that God is constantly at work in our city, nation, and the world, we must begin each day by asking…

__LORD, WHY NOT US?__

Those four words have changed everything as we, as a family of faith, have sought to be about God’s business. That prayer also might be the beginning of God-ordained transformation in your community, your church, your family, and beyond, if He chooses.

As the days grow darker and our society becomes increasingly marked by division, rancor, rebellion, and the destruction of innocent lives, it’s never been more important:
- for the hearts of God’s people to be completely His;
- for God’s people to be passionate about both holding fast to truth and advancing His Kingdom;
- and for us to continually strengthen, encourage, and admonish one another as long as it is called today, lest we be hardened by the deceitfulness of sin. (Hebrews 3:13)

So as we gather over the next few days, let us ask God to search our hearts to see where we might take new ground. Let us pray fervently for the wisdom and commitment to be bold in our leadership and our service of God’s great vision for His Church. Let’s make war against the enemies of doubt, distraction, and discouragement so our hearts are ready for the magnificent mission Our King sets before us.

I pray that our time together will be used by God to embolden and encourage you as you shepherd the flock God has entrusted you with. My hope is that a year from now, we look back and marvel at the way God moved as we humbly and continually asked Him, __LORD, WHY NOT US?__  
  
Let's go, Church!
  
Todd Wagner  
Senior Pastor, Elder
